text: Yanacucho (Quechua yana black, k'uchu corner, "black corner") is a mountain in the Vilcanota mountain range in the Andes of Peru, about high. It is situated in the Cusco Region, Canchis Province, Pitumarca District. Yanacucho lies southwest of the mountain named Comercocha and northwest of Cóndor Tuco.escale.minedu.gob.pe - UGEL map of the Quispicanchis Province 1 (Cusco Region) ==References== Category:Mountains of Peru Category:Mountains of Cusco Region
